text: Reading all the comments breaks my heart. We are all women who go through different obstacles in life and yet at the very same time we are all facing the same challenges. We all are women, we were all barbies at one time, but most importantly, we are all healing internally. Our inner childhood is a little girl in desperate need of a hug, In need of her parents apology, in need of someone explaining to her where all of her pain stems from....where all of her insecurities come from. As women , we should all be giving that inner childhood a hug and help our fellow women stand. We should be supporting each other through the pits of life and help support each other. Instead of women tearing women down we need to do the opposite and realize we are all barbies with inner childhoods in need of another friend. If we all helped each other off the ground and helped our fellow sisters by showing support...we as women would be a  lot farther in society than what we currently are if we just stopped tearing each other down and started befriending one another instead. Love you fellow barbie. You are strong, you are beautiful, you are smart, you have value, you have worth, you are creative, wonderful, passionate, and you encompass the dreams of a very important innerchild...yourself. Don't let your dreams die alongside the dreams of little girls everywhere.

text:
*(vent)*

As a 7th grader… i am touched. Elementary was so care-free, people got along so motherfucking well, and we did just everything you could think of. Now in middle school, people vape in the bathroom, starts random ass fights, anything you could think of. And the teachers keep forgetting I got ADHD and autism and I’m always getting sent to detention. People and my parents are thinking I’m bipolar due to my reoccurring depression. Speaking of parents, there was a stupid ass case where people thought my parents *ABUSED US.* I was so fucking angry. They thought my parents drugged me due to how I act. I’m anxious as fuck and I have a fucking twitching issue, what do you expect out of me?! During that case, I literally got depressed. So severely I was taken to therapy. And I was only 8 years old. (I’m 12 now for your information.) My parents are harsh, yes, but they aren’t abusive. I’ve also been through so much personally. I literally need to draw, wear something warm, listen to headphones on full blast, drink matcha tea and/or coffee, sit alone in my room, and I can’t even *DO THAT.* At home or at school. I always burst out like a bitch, but I’ve got tempermental issues. I just want to die right now. I honestly can’t take life anymore. I sometimes say to myself, “Fuck me,” or “Why do I exist,” etc. But I guess, at one point in time, I might realize that my sadness must of been useless. My old friends (I’m still friends with them, for context) have realized how sad I’ve become; they support me more than my fucking family. My boy best friend literally treats me as if I was his girlfriend, and it is in a good way. Everyone tells me, “What are you on?” “Oh my god, shut the fuck up,” “tweaker,” “it’s controllable dumbass,” etc. I feel the need that I have to apologize, but for what? I never did anything wrong. I’m only existing. Physically. But not mentally. Sadness is the only thing I feel. I’m living in pain. Awful, shitty memories come back. Every day, I wake up and I just break down crying. Painfully. My life is endangered.. by me. Due to me being in a depressed state, yet again. My parents want to take me to an asylum because I’ve attempted to kill myself and other things. But I guess, pain makes you stronger, right? It does, it tells you how alive you are. Have a good day, if you chose to read this. ❤

text:
I relate to this song so much. I literally bawled in the theater while listening to this. I was the "golden child." I was good at whatever I did. Academics, art, dance, sports, debates, inter school competitions, I never lost, always at the top. But I feel like after lockdown, I lost my spark. No matter how hard I try, I can't do anything right. I had my whole life perfectly planned out but now I am not sure about anything. I am not good at anything now. I see other people my age, and all of them seem like they are so happy and fulfilled and organized and just doing great. I don't know who I am or what I want to do in life. I am in 12th grade right now, I hope I get selected in a good good college next year. For now, I just wish things could go back to the way they were.
